  "texts": [
    "Therefore, the extent to which Criollo and Matina can be used to identify candidate resistance genes in a diverse set of cacao genotypes is unclear.",
    "To facilitate identification of novel resistance genes, we de novo assembled and annotated the Phytophthora-resistant genotype Scavina 6 (SCA 6).",
    "SCA 6 does not belong to any of the four populations sampled for this study and is thus unlikely to bias mapping rates due to relatedness.",
    "We assembled SCA 6 from 10X Genomics linked read technology [105] using a novel meta-assembly approach (\"Methods\") that created separate assemblies at multiple read depths, followed by iterative bridging between assemblies.",
    "This resulted in a highly contiguous, near-reference level genome (Scaffold N50 (Mb): 2.344; Contig N50 (Kb) 245.957), with BUSCO genome assembly completeness scores (97.2%) that indicated that most of the gene space was captured (Additional file 1: Table S4)."
  ],
